- A certain natural logarithmic threshold refers to the natural logarithm of 1000, which is approximately 6.90776;
- The production figures are averaged across the records for each energy source per year.

sql:
SELECT e.energy_source_name
FROM energy_sources e
WHERE (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.year)
    FROM energy_production_data p
    WHERE p.energy_source_id = e.energy_source_id
) = (
    SELECT COUNT(*) 
    FROM years
);
